                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d580">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/3930</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stettinius</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Director of the Office of Far Eastern
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-02">June 2,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Grew</hi>: I have read with interest and a growing
                    degree of apprehension the several memoranda and despatches which you have
                    called to my attention recently relative to the apparent growing deterioration
                    in Sino-Soviet relations and the possible development within China of a strong
                    anti-Soviet feeling.</p>
                <p>I would greatly appreciate your recommendations as to what steps could be taken
                    at this time in an effort to improve this unhappy situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>E[<hi rend="smallcaps">dward</hi>] S[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >tettinius</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
